    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-01",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Ethan"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:e60ca63202209ed6",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 178,
        "char_start": 7,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Welcome back to Practical Systems. Today we're talking about on call rotation, and I'm joined by Priya, principal SRE at a payments platform. Priya, thanks for being here.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 6000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 0,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-02",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Priya"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:13ef2f5e00a094a2",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 305,
        "char_start": 186,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Ethan. Excited for this one — incident response and on-call design is something I've been thinking about a lot.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:93e3501a7db753ca",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 514,
        "char_start": 313,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "This episode is brought to you by Linear. Linear is the issue tracker built for speed — keyboard-first, fast search, and a clean roadmap view your team actually uses. Get started at linear.com/podcast.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:9eee2478b13faffa",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 597,
        "char_start": 514,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Push back on the conventional wisdom for me. How does Notion fit into this picture?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:beca23aa3f91e200",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 859,
        "char_start": 605,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Here's how I think about it. A good on-call rotation is designed so that waking up is rare, and when it happens the response is obvious. We've seen this play out at teams using Datadog. What used to feel like an exception is honestly the median case now.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:74451bddc9887620",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 967,
        "char_start": 867,
        "episode_id": "3d0ec494-98ba-5f71-b2bd-c8559c779786",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "I want to dig into that. Where do people most often confuse correlation with causation in this area?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p02_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    }
